UAE-based global satellite operator Yahsat has connected,  Nigeria’s  teleport, satellite, and terrestrial network operator, iSAT to its Ka-band Al Yah 3 satellite service, through the services of its satellite broadband arm YahClick.<img class="size-full wp-image-1220902 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?resize=640%2C185&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="185" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?w=700&amp;ssl=1 700w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?resize=300%2C87&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?resize=58%2C17&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?resize=260%2C75&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?resize=200%2C58&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vanguard-amp-2logo.png?resize=560%2C162&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The connection agreement means that the Lagos-based iSAT will get maximum broadband capacity from Al Yah 3 satellite, which was launched in 2018.  The arrangement aims to provide iSAT’s customers in Nigeria with integrated, tailor-made solution to accommodate the changing demands and trends of the market. The addition of Ka-band HTS satellite services to ISAT’s portfolio reinforces ISAT positioning towards market-leadership in providing hybrid solutions and using relevant technology services driven by customer demand. 3 more bodies recovered, as Lagos boat mishap death toll hits 12(Opens in a new browser tab) Channels Manager at iSAT, Yomi Oluremekun said, “This addition to our portfolio builds on our strong and growing relationship with satellite operators. This further extends our infrastructure and network operations, enabling the delivery of reliable, protected, and secure communications to our customers”. VP Sales Africa at YahClick, Michael Brown, said, “We are delighted to be partnering with iSAT as a long-term client. This agreement is another example of YahClick’s rapid growth in the continent, which was further accelerated by the launch of our third satellite last year. The new satellite added 19 new markets to our existing footprint in Africa. We are thrilled that iSAT believes in our connectivity solutions, team capabilities, and commitment to the delivery of customised, bespoke services.” As part of the agreement, iSAT will have access to YahClick’s latest virtual network operator (VNO) services, which Brown said will help iSAT have full control and management over their own capacity, deliver flexibility, while providing high-speed, economical Ka-band capacity. Wizkid lands second Billboard entry with Beyoncé’s ‘Brown Skin Girl’(Opens in a new browser tab) Brown added that Yahclick’s technical team, will in addition, support iSAT to offer far-reaching broadband coverage across Nigeria. Vanguard UAE-based global satellite operator, Yahsat, reinforced its mission to bridge the gaps in the provision of ICT services across unserved and underserved regions with the announcement of a new collaboration with its Service Partners Hyperia and Zeta-Web in Nigeria. November 29, 2018 In "News" One of the world’s leading operators of communications satellites operators , Eutelsat Communications, and Yahsat, the Abu Dhabi-based international satellite operator, have signed a multi-year capacity agreement to give broadband to Africa. November 13, 2016 In "News" Perhaps, taking broadband services to rural Nigeria is about the most contentious issue in the Nigerian telecommunications industry  since a few private operators took the bold initiative to land massive submarine broadband cables into the country. October 3, 2018 In "Technol